<img src="http://biz-file.com/c/1809/457123-625x325.jpg" alt="Kwesé Zimbabwe launches promotion" width="625" height="325">© Cathy Yeulet via 123RFYet in other African countries like Ghana, Kwesé started business quite smoothly.To celebrate its one year of existence, Kwesé has come with a promotion that will offer its customers savings on a monthly subscription. The monthly subscription is normally priced at $29 but with the promotion, customers only need to pay $18. The promotion will last till the end of October.Kwesé TV is a Zimbabwean satellite and broadcasting network owned by Econet Wireless Zimbabwe, under Econet Media. On 23 August 2017, Econet Media announced that Kwesé TV was now available in Zimbabwe and that decoders were available at Econet Shops.Source: http://nextvafrica.com/.